{"id": "EUVD-2025-150372", "enisaUuid": "c48b9a7c-7649-3ae3-aaec-58b65c818e49", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nipmi: Rework user message limit handling\n\nThe limit on the number of user messages had a number of issues,\nimproper counting in some cases and a use after free.\n\nRestructure how this is all done to handle more in the receive message\nallocation routine, so all refcouting and user message limit counts\nare done in that routine.  It's a lot cleaner and safer.", "datePublished": "2025-11-12T21:56:34", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-01T06:20:05", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f63723ca7d7623f9dae1990973cd158671f03c56", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/348121b29594d42d1635648fd3ed31dfa25351d5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/53d6e403affbf6df2c859a0ea00ccfc1e72090ca", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0ed73be9a2547ffb9b5c1d879ad9bfab73d920b5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b52da4054ee0bf9ecb44996f2c83236ff50b3812", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40202"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40202"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "084e8c2d-6a5b-35c5-b56d-ba3217e88018", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.4"}, {"id": "4bac04a4-30ea-35d0-be7b-30f766941286", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.157"}, {"id": "7d6b2e74-121f-38cb-beb1-3915fffb0481", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8e76741c3d8b20dfa2d6c30fa10ff927cfd93d82 <53d6e403affbf6df2c859a0ea00ccfc1e72090ca"}, {"id": "801ce36e-5c09-32ac-a871-3063d7894416", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "802a19c1-15e6-3062-a4bb-df29d70ded81", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8e76741c3d8b20dfa2d6c30fa10ff927cfd93d82 <b52da4054ee0bf9ecb44996f2c83236ff50b3812"}, {"id": "84318020-9852-30d1-b31c-1e45515352db", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18-rc1"}, {"id": "865c4d83-c